definition: caries/rotten tooth (colloquial)/see also 齲齒|龋齿[qu3 chi3]
lower form of animal life, including insects, insect larvae, worms and similar creatures/CL:條|条[tiao2],隻|只[zhi1]/(fig.) person with a particular undesirable characteristic

sentences.english: Probing into my bad tooth with my tongue, I could feel the enlarged hole.
sentences.chinese: 我用舌頭舔我那顆蟲牙，感到牙齒上的空洞在變大。

sentences.english: Before that time I unuausal washed my tooth so I had a little decayed tooth.
sentences.chinese: 在此以前我不經常刷牙，所以我有一些蟲牙。
